                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.00/1157.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Special Commissioner</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Puerto Cortes</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-03-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 4, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Dawson reports the receipt of a telegram of this date from Dávila accepting
                    the peace arrangement; that the President and Vice President are expected to
                    resign and that Congress will elect Bertrand as first designate.</p>
            </div>
